[B] India
Date: Fri 17 Sep 2021 06:44 IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-kerala-posts-20k-cases-again-india-tally-at-35k/articleshow/86280532.cms


Kerala has reported more than 20 000 fresh cases of COVID-19 for the 1st time in 4 days, taking India's daily tally to a 6-day high of just under 35 000 on Thursday [16 Sep 2021].

India reported 34 671 new cases of the coronavirus (with Tripura's data not received until midnight), the highest daily tally since 37 868 infections were detected last Friday [10 Sep 2021], as per TOI's COVID database. Kerala's cases rose to 22 182, up from 17 681 on the previous day. The state had last reported 20 000-plus daily cases on Sunday [12 Sep 2021].

Despite Thursday's spurt [16 Sep 2021], Kerala's 7-day average of daily cases continued to decline, falling below 20 000 to 19 505. This indicates that cases in the state are still dipping.

Meanwhile, Mizoram reported 1402 new cases, the 3rd-highest daily count recorded in the state that is in the midst of a surge in infections.

India recorded 318 deaths on Thursday [16 Sep 2021], down from 375 on the previous day. Kerala reported 178 deaths, Maharashtra 45, Tamil Nadu 25, Karnataka 18, and Andhra [Pradesh] 14.

