[C] Nepal
Date: Thu 16 Sep 2021 16:49 NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/covid-19-deaths-in-nepal-cross-11000-mark-on-thursday-active-caseload-stands-at-25772


Nepal's coronavirus caseload reached 781 989 on Thursday [16 Sep 2021] with 1165 more people testing positive for the infection in the past 24 hours.

Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 745 215 with 1689 discharges logged today [16 Sep 2021]. On the other hand, the countrywide COVID-19 mortality toll increased to 11 002 with 11 more fatalities.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, a total of 15 179 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours of which 11 208 were PCR tests while 3971 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 4 068 591 PCR tests have been carried out to date [16 Sep 2021].

Similarly, antigen tests have confirmed 346 positive cases in the past 24 hours. The total number of single-day infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests amounts to 1511.

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 95.3%, while the fatality rate stands at 1.5%. The country's active COVID-19 case count currently is 25 772.

Currently, there are 220 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

The capital district holds the highest number of infections with 293 cases in the country. Morang is 2nd in line with 120 cases while Lalitpur has 98 cases today [16 Sep 2021].

