ProMED-SoAs
<promed-SoAs@promedmail.org>

[Maps of Sri Lanka: http://www.mapsopensource.com/images/sri-lanka-districts-map.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8685750,144.

The South Asian COVID-19 situation, according to data from Worldometer (https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/) as of 17 Sep 2021 at 03:24 GMT:
Country: Total cases / Total deaths / Deaths per million population
India: 33 380 522 / 444 278 / 318
Bangladesh: 1 538 203 / 27 109 / 163
Pakistan: 1 215 821 / 27 004 / 119
Nepal: 781 989 / 11 002 / 370
Sri Lanka: 498 694 / 11 817 /549
Afghanistan: 154 487 / 7186 / 180
Maldives: 83 248 / 227 / 411
Bhutan: 2596 / 3 / 4

Over the last 7 days, 217 518, 13 313, 21 623, 7402, 21 058, and 525 COVID-19 cases were detected in India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Nepal, Sri Lanka, and Afghanistan, respectively, compared with 259 715, 17 774, 22 620, 8673, 29 879, and 587 in the preceding 7 days, revealing a downward trend in India, the continuation of the sharp declining trend in Bangladesh, a slightly decreasing trend in Pakistan, a decreasing trend in Nepal, a sharp decreasing trend in Sri Lanka and a stable trend in Afghanistan with a very low number of reported cases.

Live Situational Analysis on COVID-19 cases in Sri Lanka can be seen at https://hpb.health.gov.lk/covid19-dashboard/. After a plateau over the last 2 weeks or so, the curve of the disease in Sri Lanka has seemingly started to fall sharply. This could be the effect of the country-wide lockdown, initially imposed from the night of 20 Aug 2021 to 30 Aug 2021, which has been extended in 3 phases until 21 Sep 2021 (https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/sri-lanka-extends-covid-19-lockdown-till-september-21/articleshow/86095119.cms). Because the daily reported cases are still very high to be managed clinically despite a sharp decreasing trend, the Association of Medical Specialists (AMS) in the country urged the Government to further extend the lockdown until the beginning of October (2021) (https://www.dailymirror.lk/latest_news/Health-experts-urge-Govt-to-extend-lockdown-further/342-220519). The total number of deaths associated with the disease has crossed the milestone of 11 000 in the country, and the number of the reported deaths per million population attributed to COVID-19 remains the highest in Sri Lanka compared with any other South Asian countries. However, the country has reportedly completed vaccinating over 50% of the population with 2 doses of COVID-19 vaccines (http://www.news.cn/english/2021-09/15/c_1310189735.htm).

Because daily case positivity in Pakistan is still quite high, below 6% (5.6%), as indicated in item [D] above, a slight dip in weekly reported cases over the course of the last 2 weeks or so should still be cautiously interpreted because any substantial relaxation in the personal protective measures such as mask-wearing, maintaining physical distancing, and handwashing would escalate the situation in the near future due to the ongoing spread of the delta variant. According to the data as of 14 Sep 2021, a total of 70 494 348 vaccine doses have been administered in the country (https://covid19.who.int/region/emro/country/pk).

The daily-case positivity and number of deaths associated with COVID-19 are dropping steadily in Bangladesh. The current case positivity rate is now just below 6% (5.98%), around 3% lower compared to the rate observed in the preceding week which is also the lowest in more than the last 6 months, as indicated in item [A] above. As the new cases were falling sharply, the country decided to reopen schools and colleges from 12 Sep 2021 with maintaining guidelines and health protocols (https://m.theindependentbd.com/post/267954). Bangladesh has a plan of vaccinating 80% population above the age of 18 years. So far, of the target population, only 18% have received the 1st dose and 12% have received both 1st and 2nd doses (http://103.247.238.92/webportal/pages/covid19-vaccination-update.php).

India reported a steady fall of new cases over the last 2 weeks after showing an alarming sign of an increasing trend over the preceding 2 weeks. As the number of new cases is falling in Kerala state, the total country-wide count is also showing a significant decreasing trend. Out of 36 States and Union Territories in the country, 19 including Kerala are now showing a decreasing trend of new cases, according to the counts as of 17 Sep 2021 at 08:00 IST compared to the counts in the previous 24 hours (https://www.mohfw.gov.in/). As of 17 Sep 2021, at 8.00 AM IST, 772 425 744 doses of the COVID-19 vaccine have been administered in India (https://www.mohfw.gov.in/).

